[4] California (El Dorado County)
Date: Fri 20 Jun 2014
Source: Tahoe Daily Tribune [edited]
http://www.tahoedailytribune.com/southshore/11895648-113/cases-pertussis-county-health


Health officials in El Dorado County and across California are seeing an uptick in pertussis cases and emphasizing the importance for children and adults to remain up to date on immunizations. 10 cases of pertussis, also known as whooping cough, have been reported in El Dorado County in 2014. That's more than twice the number of cases reported in 2013, County Health Officer Dr Alicia Paris-Pombo said.

6 cases were reported in South Lake Tahoe and 4 cases were reported on the West Slope. None have been fatal.

The cyclical disease typically peaks every 3 to 5 years and the last peak occurred in 2010, when El Dorado County had 54 cases and California had more than 9400 cases.

