[7) Virginia (Eastern Shore)
Date: Thu 12 Jun 2014
Source: DelmarvaNow [edited]
http://www.delmarvanow.com/story/news/local/virginia/2014/06/12/virginia-whooping-cough-pertussis/10373301/


The Eastern Shore [Accomack and Northampton counties] Health District and health care professionals throughout the Eastern Shore are urging residents to get vaccinated in the wake of an upsurge in cases of pertussis, or whooping cough, since late May 2014. "We had the 1st case -- that was in an infant -- and it quickly swelled to 10, and now we have 15 active investigations," said Dr David O Matson, director of the health district.

In comparison, only 3 cases of pertussis were diagnosed on the Eastern Shore in 2012 and one case was identified in 2013. Those recently diagnosed with pertussis on the Eastern Shore live from near the Maryland line in Accomack County to Cape Charles in Northampton County and range in age from 1 month to 50s, with the majority being infants. At least two have been hospitalized. There have been no deaths.

[Byline: Carol Vaughn]

